t to one of five design modes (interface, foundations, motion, audit, md-generator) or one nested transport packet (design-mcp-open-design) by workflowMode through mode-registry.json. The five design modes share packetKind:\\\"workflow\\\"; design-mcp-open-design is the sole packetKind:\\\"transport\\\" entry, driving the external Open Design app's od CLI and stdio MCP server without performing design judgment itself. The four doc-guidance modes cite the shared reference base (anti-slop principles, cognitive laws, design-token vocabulary) for consistent vocabulary, md-generator runs its own Playwright CSS-extraction backend, and design-mcp-open-design runs an od-cli-transport backend (backendKind discriminates all three). The hub holds no per-mode design logic; every mode keeps its own judgment, examples, and verification in its packet, and all six route by hub membership so the advisor sees exactly one design identity.\",\n    \"source_docs\": [\n      \"SKILL.md\",\n      \"mode-registry.json\"\n    ],\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-06-25T00:00:00Z\",\n    \"last_updated_at\": \"2026-06-26T00:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":165,"totalLines":165,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/graph-metadata.json","time":{"start":1783437229010,"end":1783437229020}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f9540dbb0d880ed016a4d17acd2348191a96b60cc3b4d3f2f"}},"id":"prt_f3d247b8500163xYeXVv6yZHDa","sessionID":"ses_0c2dd1dfdffet6Vx3PotxpyX20","messageID":"msg_f3d245227001CSenUBt9m5EkNE"}}
